This function begins by confirming the provided PID is still valid using `pid_exists`. If the process exists, it delegates the actual retrieval of the cmdline to the operating system-specific module within psutil.

```python
def get_process_cmdline(self):
        """Return process cmdline as a list of arguments."""
        if not pid_exists(self.pid):
            raise NoSuchProcess(self.pid, self._process_name)
        return _psutil_osx.get_process_cmdline(self.pid)
```

The command line is returned as a list directly from the OS layer. Note that because this implementation relies on platform-specific utilities, its use is restricted to systems where those modules are configured.
